Document: NavigationMeshGenerator
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationmeshgenerator.rst
Summary: This document provides an overview of the NavigationMeshGenerator class in Godot Engine.

NavigationMeshGenerator is a utility class for generating NavigationMeshes. It is not intended to be instantiated directly. Instead, its static methods are used to create and modify NavigationMeshes.

Key Rule: NavigationMeshGenerator is a static utility class and should not be instantiated.

Methods:
- bake_navigationmesh(mesh: Mesh, bake_settings: NavigationMeshBakeSettings) → NavigationMesh
  Bakes a NavigationMesh from a given Mesh resource with specified bake settings.

- bake_navigationmesh_from_surfaces(surfaces: Array, bake_settings: NavigationMeshBakeSettings) → NavigationMesh
  Bakes a NavigationMesh from an array of surfaces with specified bake settings.

- get_baked_navigationmesh_debug_mesh(mesh: Mesh, bake_settings: NavigationMeshBakeSettings) → Mesh
  Returns a debug mesh representing the baked NavigationMesh from a given Mesh resource with specified bake settings.

- get_baked_navigationmesh_debug_mesh_from_surfaces(surfaces: Array, bake_settings: NavigationMeshBakeSettings) → Mesh
  Returns a debug mesh representing the baked NavigationMesh from an array of surfaces with specified bake settings.

- is_valid_navigationmesh_bake_settings(bake_settings: NavigationMeshBakeSettings) → bool
  Checks if the provided NavigationMeshBakeSettings are valid for baking.

Inherits: Object
